reviews.review_text: Grabbed a game day Big Mac deal here. It was freshly made and for $3, a great deal! I have been to this McDonalds for decades, going back to its original location on Hastings and Alpha. This newer location is smaller, but has a more modern atmosphere. Staff are courteous, efficient, and patient. Drive thru and in-restaurant ordering experiences were always positive. Parking is plenty, but due to the elongated space, youre a little further away a lot of times. Food-wise, due to traffic volume, is more often fresh than not. Besides the Still Creek location, I find this location one of the more reliable McDonalds for consistent fresh quality food. Great spot to pop in if youre hungry for McDonalds!

Say whatever you want about McDonalds. This specific location I have been going to since I was kid. Its been there for everyone when the economy was declining, and when it was booming. McDonalds drives with the economy (not drive THE economy) because it is practical. Practicality is how a product, business, and company continues to grow. Take a good honest look at yourselves then evaluate and filter your thoughts before allowing yourself to speak negative about McDonalds. Dont over estimate yourselves, a lot of you are rich but in debt and still frequent McDonalds then trash talk about it. Warren Buffet frequents many fast food places, so why should yall speak? On that note, majority of the staff I have seen since I was 13 or 14 years old  are still here and I always find / create the opportunity to have an conversation with them.
